title.narrative: DRRR/ EMERGENCY RESPONSE

description.narrative: Emergency Programme Implementation, which contributes to Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Operations Support To Programme Delivery (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Supply And Logistics, Supply And Logistics (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Communities, parents, caregivers and children have increased awareness of the consequences of violence and have the skills to protect children and women.

title.narrative: Emergency Programme Implementation

description.narrative: Approximately 2,000 children affected by the volcanic eruption in PNG's WNB Province had received routine vaccination services including, OPV & MR vaccines, vitamin-A supplementation and nutrition interventions in 2019. The affected province was also supplied with Non-pneumatic anti-shock garments to prevent post-partum hemorrhage in pregnant women with complicated deliveries, and hypothermia devices for low birth weight babies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
